4.7 Power Systems

4.7.1 Primary Power Source

Quantum Vacuum Energy Harvesting:

· Casimir effect energy extraction: 1GW/m²
· Zero-point energy tapping: 10GW theoretical maximum
· Dark energy coupling: Experimental, potential 100GW
· Efficiency: 0.1% of theoretical maximum (1GW practical)

4.7.2 Secondary Power Sources

Starlight Collection:

· Area: 1 km² photovoltaic surface
· Efficiency: 35% multi-junction cells
· Power: 350MW in habitable zone

Thermal Gradients:

· Hull temperature differential: 300K to 3K
· Thermoelectric conversion: 10% efficiency
· Power: 100MW

4.7.3 Energy Storage

Superconducting Magnetic Energy Storage (SMES):

· Capacity: 100GJ (27.8 MWh)
· Discharge rate: 10GW for 10 seconds
· Efficiency: 95% round-trip

Quantum Batteries:

· Capacity: 1TJ (277.8 MWh)
· Charge/discharge: 1 second
· Principle: Quantum coherence energy storage

4.7.4 Power Distribution

Wireless Power Transfer:

· Efficiency: 90% at 100m distance
· Frequency: 2.4 GHz resonant coupling
· Safety: Directed beams with obstacle detection

Superconducting Transmission:

· Loss: <0.1% per km
· Current: 100kA at 10kV
· Cooling: Microfluidic helium circulation

4.8 Communication Systems

4.8.1 Quantum Communication

Quantum Entanglement Network:

· Range: Unlimited (theoretical)
· Bandwidth: 1Gbit/second per entangled pair
· Security: Perfect, intercept detection probability 1.0
· Latency: Instantaneous (within measurement constraints)

Quantum Key Distribution (QKD):

· Protocol: BB84 with decoy states
· Rate: 1Mbit/second at 1000km
· Security: Information-theoretic proof

4.8.2 Classical Communication

Laser Optical Communication:

· Bandwidth: 1Tbit/second
· Range: 10 light-years with 1m telescopes
· Modulation: Quadrature amplitude modulation (4096-QAM)
· Error correction: Turbo codes with 10⁻¹² BER

Radio Communication:

· Frequency: 1-100 GHz
· Power: 1MW transmitters
· Antennas: 100m phased array
· Data rate: 1Gbit/second at 1 light-year

4.8.3 Network Architecture

Interstellar Network Protocol (INP):

· Store-and-forward with predictive routing
· Error tolerance: Months of disruption
· Priority: Scientific data > crew communication > system updates
· Compression: 1000:1 lossless for typical data

4.9 Sensor Systems

